What is a Row?
Simple definition: A widget that arranges its children horizontally (left to right), like items on a shelf.

Think of it like: A horizontal <div> in HTML with display: flex; flex-direction: row;

===============Row vs Column===========================================================
Feature	                           Row	                     Column
Direction	                         Horizontal (→)	           Vertical (↓)
mainAxisAlignment	                 Left to right	           Top to bottom
crossAxisAlignment	               Top to bottom	           Left to right
When to use	                       Side-by-side items	       Stacked items
=======================================================================================


[[[[[[The 5 Most Important Concepts]]]]]]


1️⃣ children (Widgets Inside)
What it does: The widgets arranged horizontally.

dart
Row(
  children: [
    Text('Left'),
    Text('Middle'),
    Text('Right'),
  ],
)
Result: [Left] [Middle] [Right]



2️⃣ mainAxisAlignment (Horizontal Alignment)
What it does: How children are spaced horizontally.

Value	                             What It Does
MainAxisAlignment.start            Children at the left (default)
MainAxisAlignment.center	         Children in the middle
MainAxisAlignment.end	             Children at the right
MainAxisAlignment.spaceEvenly	     Equal space between, before, and after
MainAxisAlignment.spaceBetween	   Equal space between children only
MainAxisAlignment.spaceAround	     Equal space around each child



3️⃣ crossAxisAlignment (Vertical Alignment)
What it does: How children are aligned vertically within the row.

Value	                            What It Does
CrossAxisAlignment.start	        Align to the top
CrossAxisAlignment.center	        Align to the center (default)
CrossAxisAlignment.end	          Align to the bottom
CrossAxisAlignment.stretch	      Stretch to fill the full height
CrossAxisAlignment.baseline 	    Align by text baseline




4️⃣ Expanded (Fill Remaining Space)
What it does: Makes a child take up all remaining horizontal space.

dart
Row(
  children: [
    Text('Fixed'),
    Expanded(  // ← Takes all remaining space
      child: Text('Expands to fill'),
    ),
    Text('Fixed'),
  ],
)
Result: [Fixed] [Expands to fill ] [Fixed]




5️⃣ TextDirection (Left-to-Right or Right-to-Left)
What it does: Controls the direction children are rendered.

dart
// Left to right (default)
Row(
  textDirection: TextDirection.ltr,
  children: [Text('A'), Text('B'), Text('C')],
)  // Result: [A] [B] [C]





// Right to left
Row(
  textDirection: TextDirection.rtl,
  children: [Text('A'), Text('B'), Text('C')],
)  // Result: [C] [B] [A]













